    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1672444293\"><html>\n  <head>\n\n    \n  </head>\n  \n    I created a <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://java.net/projects/javamail/sources/mercurial/content/mail/src/test/java/com/sun/mail/test/ClassLoaderSuite.java\">ClassLoaderSuite</a>\n    to do this for JavaMail testing several years ago.<br>\n    <br>\n    David Saff <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ygrps-yiv-1672444293moz-txt-link-abbreviated\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:saff@...\">saff@...</a> [junit] wrote on 05/19/15 11:01:\n    <blockquote><span title=\"qreply\"> <blockquote\n\n type=\"cite\"> <span style=\"display:none;\">&nbsp;</span>\n      \n          <div id=\"ygrps-yiv-1672444293ygrp-text\">\n            <div dir=\"ltr\">You should be able to do it with a custom\n              Runner.&nbsp; As Aaron pointed out, Robolectric does it, and\n              I&#39;d definitely recommend poking around their code a bit.&nbsp;\n              I don&#39;t think any patches to JUnit should be necessary.</div>\n            <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-1672444293gmail_extra\"><br>\n              <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-1672444293gmail_quote\">On Tue, May 19, 2015 at 7:11 AM,\n                Malte Finsterwalder <a rel=\"nofollow\"\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:malte@...\">malte@...</a>\n                [junit] <span dir=\"ltr\">&lt;<a rel=\"nofollow\"\n target=\"_blank\" href=\"mailto:junit@yahoogroups.com\">junit@yahoogroups.com</a>&gt;</span>\n                wrote:<br>\n                <blockquote class=\"ygrps-yiv-1672444293gmail_quote\" style=\"border-left:1px #ccc solid;\">\n                  <div style=\"background-color:#fff;\">\n                    <span>&nbsp;</span>\n                    <div>\n                      <div>\n                        <div>\n                          <div dir=\"ltr\">Hi Johannes,\n                            <div><br>\n                            </div>\n                            <div>I&#39;m totally on Dawids side: Why do you\n                              need custom classloading?</div>\n                            <div>On the other hand, if you really,\n                              really need it, you may be able to realize\n                              it by wrapping surefire or JUnit (or both)\n                              somehow. And there is always\n                              bytecode-manipulation. :-)</div>\n                            <div>But then again: JUnit is no magic. You\n                              could even write your own very simple test\n                              execution framework for your particular\n                              problem. And you could even base it on\n                              JUnits capabilities.</div>\n                            <div>Just to spray some more ideas...</div>\n                            <div><br>\n                            </div>\n                            <div>Greetings,</div>\n                            <div>&nbsp; &nbsp;Malte</div>\n                            &#8203;</div>\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                </blockquote>\n              </div>\n              <br>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          \n      \n      \n    </blockquote>\n    <br>\n  \n</span></blockquote></html>\n</div>", 
